\">Lovley, Erika. [https://web.archive.org/web/20090907074150/http://www.politico.com/news/stories/1008/14751.html \"Czar (n): An insult; a problem-solver\"], ''Politico'', Oct 21, 2008, ''archived by WebCite''. Office of Press Secretary [https://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/news/releases/2004/04/20040408-2.html  \"Personnel Announcement \"], Apr 8, 2004.</ref>\n|2004\u20132006\n|(New position), President appointed\n|{{sortname|George W.|Bush}}\n|\n|-\n|birth control czar\n|Deputy Assistant Secretary of Population Affairs, [[Department of Health and Human Services]]\n|[[Eric Keroack|Keroack, Eric]]<ref name=\"keroackerik\">Schaeffer, Amanda. [http://www.slate.com/id/2154249/ \"The Family Un-Planner, The Bush administration's crazy new HHS appointment\"], ''[[Slate Magazine]]'', Nov 21, 2006. Lloyd, Carol. [http://www.salon.com/mwt/broadsheet/2007/05/31/birth_control/print.html \"Pharmacy protects women from contraception.\"], ''Salon.com'', May 31, 2007. Estes, Andrea.[http://www.boston.com/news/local/articles/2007/04/07/doctor_who_quit_us_post_was_warned_by_state \"Doctor who quit US post was warned by state\"], ''Boston Globe'', Apr 7, 2007.</ref>\n|2006\u20132007\n|President appointed\n|{{sortname|George W.|Bush}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Mexico \u2013 United States border|border]] czar\n|[[U.S. attorney]] and Special Representative for the Southwest Border, [[United States Department of Justice|Department of Justice]]\n|[[Alan Bersin|Bersin, Alan]]<ref name=\"bersinalan1998\">Ellingwood, Ken. [http://articles.latimes.com/1998/jun/28/news/mn-64534 \"'Border Czar' Ends a Highly Visible Reign\"], ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', Jun 28, 1998.</ref>\n|1995\u20131998\n|President nominated, Senate confirmed as U.S. Attorney, Appointed as Special Representative\n|{{sortname|Bill|Clinton}}\n|\u2713\n|-\n|border czar\n|Assistant Secretary for International Affairs,  Special Representative for Border Affairs, [[US Department of Homeland Security|Dept of Homeland Security]],\n|Bersin, 