ar&source=bl&ots=JprK4l_tAJ&sig=7e891H7Dh-0wPgtmYkCAW3hpM2Q&hl=en&ei=UOSoSrCRJcaUnQfSqI2bBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1#v=onepage&q=fred%20vinson%20czar&f=false \"Chief Justice Fred M. Vinson of Kentucky: a political biography\"], ''Univ Press of Kentucky'', 2002, p. xii.</ref>\n|1943\u20131945\n|President appointed\n|{{sortname|Franklin|Roosevelt}}\n|\n|-\n|economic czar\n|Director, Office of Economic Stabilization\n|[[William Hammatt Davis|Davis, William Hammatt]]<ref name=\"daviswilliam\">[http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,790873,00.html \"FOOD: The Tenth Czar\"], ''Time'', Apr 5, 1943. [http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,850049-1,00.html \"US At War: Men Around Byrnes\"], Oct 19, 1942. ''American Presidency Project.'' [http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/?pid=16171 Exec order establishing the office], Oct 3, 1942.</ref>\n|1945\u20131946\n|President appointed\n|{{sortname|Franklin|Roosevelt}}\n|\n|-\n|economic czar, big-picture economic czar\n|Chairman, [[Economic Recovery Advisory Board]]\n|[[Paul A. Volcker|Volcker, Paul A.]]<ref name=\"volkerpaul\">Hamburger, Tom and Parsons, Christi. [http://articles.latimes.com/2009/mar/05/nation/na-obama-czars5?pg=1 \"President Obama's czar system concerns some\"], ''Los Angeles Times'', Mar 5, 2009. Coile, Zachary. [http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2009/01/11/MNEJ156C9M.DTL&feed=rss.news \"Obama's big task: managing the best, brightest\"], ''San Francisco Chronicle'', Jan 11, 2009.</ref>\n|2009\n|President appointed\n|{{sortname|Barack|Obama}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Energy Czar|energy czar]]\n|Director of the Energy Policy Office\n|[[John Arthur Love|Love, John Arthur]]<ref name=\"lovejohn\">Lovley, Erika. [http://www.politico.com/news/stories/1008/14751.html \"Czar (n): An insult; a problem-solver\"], ''Politico'', Oct 21, 2008. [http://www.nixonlibrary.gov/forresearchers/find/textual/central/smof/epo.php Energy Policy Office] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/200912161